                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d955">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 714.1515/23</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Leavell</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-07T17:00:00-06:02">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your instruction number 159, of July 6 last. Before I could find opportunity to
                    present this matter to the President, he sent the Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    to inform me that the Honduran authorities having moved in this matter, he was
                    sending to Honduras a special representative to treat of it in the hope that it
                    can be amicably arranged. The Minister for Foreign Affairs will communicate
                    further with me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leavell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
